title: Social security; key figures
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: social-security-key-figures
notes:
This table shows actual key figures of benefits concerning labour disablement, unemployment, income support, support for surviving relatives and child support.
It also shows figures concerning old age pensions, family allowances, early retirement and loss of working time due tot illness (sick leave).

Data available from: January 1998.

Status of the figures: 
- the figures in this table can be definitive or provisional;
- the figures concerning loss of working time due to illness as from 2008 are provisional.

Changes as of May 1, 2013
Added is
the annual average of 2012 of income support  
The following provisional figures have become definitive
-the figures concerning income support

Changes as of March 27, 2013
Added are the provisional figures of
- the benefits concerning labour disablement (total number, WAO, WAZ, Wajong, IVA and WGA) of December 2012 and the annual averages of 2012;
- the benefits concerning the general Family Allowance Act (AKW) of December 2012 and the annual averages of 2012;  
- the benefits concerning the Old Age Pensions Act (AOW) of January and February 2013;
- sick leave of December 2012 and the annual averages of 2012.

The following provisional figures have become definitive
- the figures of the benefits concerning labour disablement (total number, WAO, WAZ, Wajong, IVA and WGA) of October 2012;
- the figures of the benefits concerning the general Family Allowances Act (AKW) of September 2012;
- the figures of the benefits concerning the Old Age Pensions Act (AOW) of November and December 2012 and the annual averages of 2012.

When will new figures be published? New figures will be published in May 2013.
